content:
Let me start off saying I’m a huge fan of the previous Logitech wheels G25 & G27 for the PC they were the best bang for the buck. Unfortunately Logitech was a bit late to the gaming console party with a wheel so I popped for a Thrustmaster TX Racing Wheel when they first came out which is great now because I really can compare the two.

The Good;
The wheel force feedback feels great!!! The one thing I noticed immediately is how much lighter of a feel there is between the Thrustmaster TX vs the Logitech G920 and for me this is a good thing!!!  The Thrustmaster steering always felt heavy to me, I know this is just a user experience thing but I genuinely felt it slowed my steering reaction times. So if you liked the way a G25 or G27 felt, then you will feel right at home again!

The Bad;
Yes, just like any other reviewer of this product, the brake pedal stiffness is ridiculous! I will give it some time and see if it softens up or I will end up with a Popeye calf muscle!

The Ugly;
Whose dumb idea was it to put a bright white LED that shines in your face!!???? I guess nobody at Logitech plays games in the dark!!??

Of note;
I really miss the thumb accessible buttons the G25 & G27 had, the only button my thumb can really reach is the “B” Button, the “LSB” and “RSB” buttons are really positioned to low. Although I give high praise to Logitech for black letters and symbols on a white button!!!
Wheel still mounts up perfectly to a PlaySeat Evolution perfectly…thank you Logitech!
Unfortunately there is NO left right adjustment on the foot pedals , not that there was with the G25 or G27 but I have been spoiled by the Thrustmaster T3PA pedals which have multiple mounting holes in the pedals
